21:
Well, nice to meet you there, Stella!
I'm Marchella!
23:
So, what are you doing around
these parts? You don't have the
uniform on, so I figure you're not a
student.
26:
I heard some beautiful music
coming from here. Was that you?
31:
Oh! Are you maybe a transfer
student looking to join our club?!
35:
Hmm, no, I'm not getting that
impression either. Anyway, let me fill
you in!
38:
We are the Voluntas Arcane Arts
Academy's official Marching Band
Club!
42: And I happen to be its drum major!
49:
Ooh, are you interested? You should
come along! We're just about done
with sectionals!
54:
Great work on those sectional
rehearsals, everyone!
58:
All right, I want some extra pep in
you todayâ€”we've got ourselves a
real cutie patootie spectating!
63:
Let's get started! Remember
everyone, we're here to have fun!
82:
Well, Stella? What did you think of
our performance?
86: It was amazing. Very, very amazing.
90:
Hehe, now that's a reaction I'm
happy to hearâ€”especially given
how hard everyone's been working!
93:
Being in a marching band isn't all
about playing your instrument well,
you know. The most important thing
is teamwork.
95:
Everything needs to come together
in perfect harmonyâ€”your pitch, your
movements... It's like like you're
building something bigger than
yourself!
99:
...It's the drum major's job to tie it all
together, but I've still got a long way
to go.
103:
You looked like you were having a
lot of fun.
108:
Haha, that's because I definitely
WAS!
111:
And if I want it to be even more fun,
I've got put in even MORE effort!
114:
I had a sneaking suspicion you were
behind this, Marchella.
121:
Judging by that reaction, I'm
guessing you know exactly why I'm
here.
130:
You're not going to sheepishly laugh
your way out of this one! Come on,
time for a supplementary lecture.
134:
So when the band marches, magic
spells can be activated without
incantations? Seriously?
137:
It shocked me too when I saw it for
the first time.
140:
All the other teachers couldn't be
bothered to handle the situation, so
for some inexplicable reason I was
put in charge of guiding her.
144:
So you guys were actually friends of
Professor Nicola! I'm sorry I mistook
you for a transfer student, Stella.
148:
It's okay. It was very fun spending
time with you.
152:
If you're adventurers, then that
means you've probably been
outside of Palpebra and the
Kaleidscope, right?
154:
I... have a favor to ask, if you don't
mind.
158:
Could you let me into your group? It
can be our secret!
161:
Do you want to become an
adventurer, Marchella?
165: Hmm... I mean, not exactly, but...
168:
The grass is always greener on the
other side, you know? I feel like I
can't just always do what I wantâ€”I
have to try new things!
172:
I won't be a burden to you, don't
worry! I'm really good at using
support magicâ€”even students at
the top of my class praise me!
180: Really?! Thank you so much, Stella!
185:
You've certainly got guts, flagrantly
talking about breaking school rules
right in front of your teacher.
192:
Just make sure you come up with a
good excuse for the other professors.
201:
Yes. This academy is too small a
world for her. She'll need to think
bigger if she's to realize her potential.
204:
This is a good opportunity for that.
Can I ask you to look after her?
212:
Thanks, Alk! I can't wait to go
adventuring together!
216:
I'm going to give this my absolute
best!
